deck: Gavin Land is a man seeking vengeance upon the human monster that defiled and destroyed his family.
description: Gavin Land was a regular guy - father, a husband, a suburbanite – before the world ended. But before the first infection, a different kind of monster defiled and killed his daughter, destroyed his family, and tortured him with what had been done. Land changed into a messenger of vengeance and lived only to kill the people that had done this to him. When the Crossed outbreak hit, it made it both easier and harder for his vision of revenge to be seen through. Now he has to fight through a world of maniacs but the upside is that none of them care if he is an insane, murdering, madman now.
name: Gavin Land

description:
Origin

He is a Brain Dog that first appears in the pilot episode. He alerts the Bravest Warriors of the dangerous tickle monster invading his planet.

Personality

He is very intelligent, and therefore unable to express any emotion.

Appearance

He has a lumpy head that resembles a brain. He wears a light-blue shirt with a yellow striped tie, and has 2 pens in his pocket protector. Unlike most of the other members of his species, he wears glasses.

deck: Piper McLean is the demigod daughter of Aphrodite. After joining Camp Half Blood, she ventured to Europe to fight the giants, eventually forcing their leader, Gaea, to sleep with her charmspeak. She is currently in a relationship with Jason Grace.
description:
Background

Piper is half Native American, half god. Her father Tristan McLean is a famous movie star, and her mother is an Olympian goddess. Her Grandpa Tom used to tell her Native American stories, which she often relates to Greek mythology.

Powers

Charmspeak: Piper's voice can persuade others to do her bidding. She first used it to steal cars or get out of trouble, and it used to be limited to people without magic resistance. Following the Lost Hero, however, her charmspeak has become more versatile and efficacious. Now she is capable of:

Probability Manipulation (limited): Piper once forced a giantess to miss with her knife

Reality Warping (limited): Gave a mechanical dragon sentience

Her most notable feat with charmspeak is defeating Gaea, the Greek representation of the Earth.

Paraphernalia

Katoptris: Piper has a knife called Katoptris, which she can use to see the past, present, and future. It should be noted, however, that she has very limited control over the blade.

Sword of the Boreads: Following Zethes' defeat in the Mark of Athena, Piper picked up his sword, which gives her limited Cryokinesis, though she has not shown any degree of proficiency with the sword's powers.
name: Piper McLean

description:
Pirouette is a young girl that has been raised in a circus. After one night when the circus passed through Lima, Ohio, a couple left a small baby with a group of clowns. Judging that they were too far to turn back the clowns decided to raise the child. Unknown to her for some time was the fact that the circus is in some ways a front for criminal activity, either pickpocketing or burglary. She is raised in this environment and treated as a child by most performers, though she is kept closest to the clowns, though she is abused harshly by them. She is told to always wear her makeup so that the scars and bruises from their abuse do not show. Upon returning to Lima, she decides to run away and find her family.

Due to being raised in a circus, she exhibits a number of skills well beyond that of a girl her age, including acrobatics and gymnastics at a level better than those trained for the circus in those roles. She is also an adept thief.
name: Pirouette

deck: One of Cinderella's mice who was turned into a man.
description:
Marcel was one of the mice that was turned into a human when the fairy godmother used her magic to prepare Cinderella for the ball. Instead of waiting by the coach like the other mice-turned-men, Marcel snuck into the ball and, when the clock struck midnight, he was allowed to remain a human due to a loophole in the spell. He spent his human life mating with as many women as he could find, often producing human/mouse hybrid children as a result.

At the end of the Of Men and Mice storyline, Marcel was returned to mouse form and blinded in the process. He is now part of the Three Blind Mice.
